"Abstract Last month, in Part 1 of this series of articles examining the Changing Face of International Cryptography Policy, we looked at recent developments in France. As I noted then, French and British policy in this area have tended to align more and more closely during the past decade, especially in respect of the use and licensing of Trusted Third Parties (TTPs) for the escrow of encryption keys as well as the related fight against organized crime and terrorism."
